result.name: Wa Yat Shanghai Restaurant

reviews.text: Quality pretty marginal.
Delicious but interior looks old.
Overpriced and extremely small portions. Hot and sours soup tastes like straight vinegar
Love the noodle. best in town.

Chaotic Shanghainese joint in Sheung Wan! 

Come here for lunch sometimes, the food is so good and it's also very affordable. I ordered a bowl of hot peanut sauce/spicy noodles 擔擔麵 with pork and it was so good. It was flavorful and the portion quite large. 

Most people have to share tables with strangers but this happens a lot in financial districts during lunch hour. I would recommend people to order a portion of Shanghai steamed dumplings aka xlb~ They are steaming hot and full of soup.
